slokas_no,slokas,slokas_translated
1,सञ्जय उवाचतं तथा कृपयाविष्टमश्रुपूर्णाकुलेक्षणम् ।विषीदन्तमिदं वाक्यमुवाच मधुसूदनः ॥ १ ॥,"Sanjaya said: To him who was thus overwhelmed with compassion, whose eyes were filled with tears and agitated, Madhusudana (Krishna) spoke these words."
2,श्री भगवानुवाचकुतस्त्वा कश्मलमिदं विषमे समुपस्थितम् ।अनार्यजुष्टमस्वर्ग्यकीर्तिकरमर्जुन ॥ २ ॥,"The Blessed Lord said: From where has this dejection come upon you at this critical moment, Arjuna? It is not befitting an honorable person, nor does it lead to heaven; it brings infamy."
3,क्ल‍ैब्यं मा स्म गमः पार्थ नैतत्त्वय्युपपद्यते ।क्षुद्रं हृदयदौर्बल्यं त्यक्त्वोत्तिष्ठ परन्तप ॥ ३ ॥,"Do not yield to unmanliness, O Partha, it does not befit you. Cast off this base faint-heartedness and arise, O scorcher of foes."
4,अर्जुन उवाचकथं भीष्ममहं संख्ये द्रोणं च मधुसूदन ।इषुभिः प्रतियोत्स्यामि पूजार्हावरिसूदन ॥ ४ ॥,"Arjuna said: How can I, O Madhusudana, counterattack with arrows in battle against Bhishma and Drona, who are worthy of my worship, O destroyer of enemies?"
5,गुरूनहत्वा हि महानुभावान्श्रेयो भोक्तुं भैक्ष्यमपीह लोके ।हत्वार्थकामांस्तु गुरूनिहैवभुज्ज‍ीय भोगान्‍रुधिरप्रदिग्धान् ॥ ५ ॥,"It is better to live in this world by begging than to kill the great-souled teachers. But if I kill my teachers, even in this world, all my enjoyments will be tainted with blood."
6,न चैतद्विद्मः कतरन्नो गरीयोयद्वा जयेम यदि वा नो जयेयुः ।यानेव हत्वा न जिजीविषाम-स्तेऽवस्थिताः प्रमुखे धार्तराष्ट्राः ॥ ६ ॥,"We do not know which is better for us: whether we should conquer them or they should conquer us. Those very sons of Dhritarashtra, after slaying whom we do not wish to live, stand before us in battle."
7,कार्पण्यदोषोपहतस्वभावःपृच्छामि त्वां धर्मसम्मूढचेताः ।यच्छ्रेयः स्यान्निश्‍चितं ब्रूहि तन्मेशिष्यस्तेऽहं शाधि मां त्वां प्रपन्नम् ॥ ७ ॥,"Overcome by the flaw of cowardice and confused in mind about my duty, I ask you for guidance. Tell me clearly what is best for me. I am your disciple, surrendered to you; please instruct me."
8,न हि प्रपश्यामि ममापनुद्याद् -यच्छोकमुच्छोषणमिन्द्रियाणाम् ।अवाप्य भूभावसपत्‍नमृद्धंराज्यं सुराणामपि चाधिपत्यम् ॥ ८ ॥,"I do not see anything that would remove my grief which is drying up my senses, even if I were to obtain a prosperous kingdom on earth without rivals or even sovereignty over the gods."
9,सञ्जय उवाचएवमुक्त्वा हृषीकेशं गुडाकेशः परन्तपः ।न योत्स्य इति गोविन्दामुक्त्वा तूष्णीं बभूव ह ॥ ९ ॥,"Sanjaya said: Having spoken thus to Hrishikesha, Gudakesha, the scorcher of foes, declared to Govinda, ""I will not fight,"" and became silent."
10,तमुवाच हृषीकेशः प्रहसन्निव भारत ।सेनयोरूभयोर्मध्ये विषीदन्तमिदं वचः ॥ १० ॥,"Hrishikesha, smiling as it were, spoke these words to the despondent one, O Bharata, in the midst of the two armies."
11,श्री भगवानुवाचअशोच्यनन्वशोचस्त्वं प्रज्ञावादांश्च भाषसे ।गतासूनगतासूंश्च नानुशोचन्ति पण्डिताः ॥ ११ ॥,"The Blessed Lord said: You grieve for those who should not be grieved for, yet speak words of wisdom. The wise do not mourn for the living or the dead."
12,न त्वेवाहं जातु नासं न त्वं नेमे जनाधिपाः ।न चैव नभविष्यामः सर्वे वयमतः परम् ॥ १२ ॥,"Never was there a time when I did not exist, nor you, nor all these kings; nor in the future shall any of us cease to be."
13,देहिनोऽस्मिन्यथा देहे कौमारं यौवनं जरा ।तथा देहान्तरप्राप्तिर्धीरस्तत्र न मुह्यति ॥ १३ ॥,"Just as the embodied soul passes, in this body, from childhood to youth to old age, so also does it pass into another body; the wise are not deluded by this."
14,मात्रास्पर्शास्तु कौन्तेय शीतोष्णसुखदुःखदाः ।आगमापायिनोऽनित्यास्तांस्तितिक्षस्व भारत ॥ १४ ॥,"The contacts of the senses, O son of Kunti, which give rise to cold and heat, pleasure and pain, are transitory; they come and go. Endure them, O Bharata."
15,यं हि न व्यथयन्त्येते पुरुषं पुरुषर्षभ ।समदुःखसुखं धीरं सोऽमृतत्वाय कल्पते ॥ १५ ॥,"The person whom these do not distress, O best among men, who is the same in pleasure and pain, who is steadfast, is fit for immortality."
16,नासतो विद्यते भावो नाभावो विद्यते सतः ।उभयोरपि दृष्टोऽन्तस्त्वनयोस्तत्त्वदर्शिभिः ॥ १६ ॥,The unreal has no being; there is no non-being of the real. The seers of truth have concluded the distinction between these two.
17,अविनाशि तु तद्विद्धि येन सर्वमिदं ततम् ।विनाशमव्ययस्यास्य न कश्चित्कर्तुमर्हति ॥ १७ ॥,Know that to be indestructible by which all this is pervaded. No one can bring about the destruction of this imperishable.
18,अन्तवन्त इमे देहा नित्यस्योक्ताः शरीरिणः ।अनाशिनोऽप्रमेयस्य तस्माद्युध्यस्व भारत ॥ १८ ॥,"These bodies are perishable, but the embodied soul is eternal, indestructible, and immeasurable. Therefore, O Bharata, fight."
19,य एनं वेत्ति हन्तारं यश्चैनं मन्यते हतम् ।उभौ तौ न विजानीतो नायं हन्ति न हन्यते ॥ १९ ॥,"He who thinks that the soul kills, and he who thinks of it as killed, are both ignorant. The soul kills not, nor is it killed."
20,न जायते म्रियते वा कदाचि-न्नायं भूत्वा भविता वा न भूयः ।अजो नित्यः शाश्वतोऽयं पुराणोन हन्यते हन्यमाने शरीरे ॥ २० ॥,"It is never born, nor does it ever die; nor, having once existed, does it ever cease to be. Unborn, eternal, ever-existing, and primeval, it is not slain when the body is slain."
21,वेदाविनाशिनं नित्यं य एनमजमव्ययम् ।कथं स पुरुषः पार्थ कं घातयति हन्ति कम् ॥ २१ ॥,"The soul is indestructible, eternal, unborn, and unchanging. How can that person, O Arjuna, kill or cause anyone to be killed?"
22,वासांसि जीर्णानि यथा विहायनवानि गृह्णाति नरोऽपराणि ।तथा शरीराणि विहाय जीर्णा-न्यन्यानि संयाति नवानि देही ॥ २२ ॥,"Just as a person discards worn-out garments and puts on new ones, similarly, the soul discards old bodies and takes on new ones."
23,नैनं छिन्दन्ति शस्त्राणि नैनं दहति पावकः ।न चैनं क्ल‍ेदयन्त्यापो न शोषयति मारुतः ॥ २३ ॥,"Weapons do not cut it, fire does not burn it, water does not wet it, and wind does not dry it."
24,अच्छेद्योऽयमदाह्योऽयमक्ल‍ेद्योऽशोष्य एव च ।नित्यः सर्वगतः स्थाणुरचलोऽयं सनातनः ॥ २४ ॥,"This cannot be cut, this cannot be burned, this cannot be wetted, nor can it be dried. It is eternal, all-pervading, stable, immovable, and ancient."
25,अव्यक्तोऽयमचिन्त्योऽयमविकार्योऽयमुच्यते ।तस्मादेवं विदित्वैनं नानुशोचितुमर्हसि ॥ २५ ॥,"This is unmanifest, this is inconceivable, and this is unchangeable, it is said. Therefore, knowing this, you should not grieve."
26,अथ चैनं नित्यजातं नित्यं वा मन्यसे मृतम् ।तथापि त्वं महाबाहो नैनं शोचितुमर्हसि ॥ २६ ॥,"If, however, you think of it as constantly born and constantly dying, even then, O mighty-armed, you should not grieve for it."
27,जातस्य हि ध्रुवो मृत्युर्ध्रुवं जन्म मृतस्य च ।तस्मादपरिहार्येऽर्थे न त्वं शोचितुमर्हसि ॥ २७ ॥,"For one who is born, death is certain, and for one who has died, birth is certain. Therefore, you should not grieve over the inevitable."
28,अव्यक्तादीनि भूतानि व्यक्तमध्यानि भारत ।अव्यक्तनिधनान्येव तत्र का परिदेवना ॥ २८ ॥,"All beings are unmanifest in their beginning, manifest in their middle state, and unmanifest again when annihilated. So what is there to lament?"
29,आश्चर्यवत्पश्यति कश्चिदेन -माश्चर्यवद्वदति तथैव चान्यः ।आश्चर्यवच्च‍ैनमन्यः श‍ृणोतिश्रुत्वाप्येनं वेद न चैव कश्चित् ॥ २९ ॥,"Someone sees it as a wonder; similarly, another speaks of it as a wonder. Another hears of it as a wonder, but even after hearing, no one truly knows it."
30,देही नित्यमवध्योऽयं देहे सर्वस्य भारत ।तस्मात्सर्वाणि भूतानि न त्वं शोचितुमर्हसि ॥ ३० ॥,"The soul is eternally indestructible in the body of all, O Bharata (Arjuna). Therefore, you should not grieve for any creature."
31,स्वधर्ममपि चावेक्ष्य न विकम्पितुमर्हसि ।धर्म्याद्धि युद्धाच्छ्रेयोऽन्यत्क्षत्रियस्य न विद्यते ॥ ३१ ॥,"Considering your own duty, you should not waver, for there is nothing better for a Kshatriya than a righteous battle."
32,यदृच्छया चोपपन्नं स्वर्गद्वारमपावृतम् ।सुखिनः क्षत्रियाः पार्थ लभन्ते युद्धमीदृशम् ॥ ३२ ॥,"The fortunate Kshatriyas, O Partha, obtain such a battle which comes of its own accord, an open door to heaven."
33,अथ चेत्त्वमिमं धर्म्यं सङ्ग्रामं न करिष्यसि ।ततः स्वधर्मं कीर्तिं च हित्वा पापमवाप्स्यसि ॥ ३३ ॥,"But if you do not engage in this righteous battle, then, abandoning your duty and honor, you will incur sin."
34,अकीर्तिं चापि भूतानि कथयिष्यन्ति तेऽव्ययाम् ।सम्भावितस्य चाकीर्तिर्मरणादतिरिच्यते ॥ ३४ ॥,"And people will also speak of your everlasting infamy. For one who has been honored, dishonor is worse than death."
35,भयाद्रणादुपरतं मंस्यन्ते त्वां महारथाः ।येषां च त्वं बहुमतो भूत्वा यास्यसि लाघवम् ॥ ३५ ॥,"The great warriors will think that you have withdrawn from the battle out of fear, and having been highly esteemed by them, you will fall into disrepute."
36,अवाच्यवादांश्च बहून्वदिष्यन्ति तवाहिताः ।निन्दन्तस्तव सामर्थ्य ततो दुःखतरं नु किम् ॥ ३६ ॥,"Your enemies will speak many unbecoming words about you, slandering your ability. What could be more painful than that?"
37,हतो वा प्राप्स्यसि स्वर्ग जित्वा वा भोक्ष्यसे महीम् ।तस्मादुत्तिष्ठ कौन्तेय युद्धाय कृतनिश्चयः ॥ ३७ ॥,"If you are slain, you will attain heaven; if you are victorious, you will enjoy the earth. Therefore, arise, O son of Kunti, resolved to fight."
38,सुखदुःखे समे कृत्वा लाभालाभौ जयाजयौ ।ततो युद्धाय युज्यस्व नैवं पापमवाप्स्यसि ॥ ३८ ॥,"Having made pleasure and pain, gain and loss, victory and defeat the same, then engage in battle. Thus, you will not incur sin."
39,एषा तेऽभिहिता सांख्ये बुद्धिर्योगे त्विमां श‍ृणु ।बुद्ध्या युक्तो यया पार्थ कर्मबन्धं प्रहास्यसि ॥ ३९ ॥,"This intelligence has been explained to you in the context of Sankhya; now listen to it in the context of Yoga. O Partha, equipped with this intelligence, you will free yourself from the bondage of actions."
40,नेहाभिक्रमनाशोऽस्ति प्रत्यवायो न विद्यते ।स्वल्पमप्यस्य धर्मस्य त्रायते महतो भयात् ॥ ४० ॥,"In this endeavor, there is no loss of effort, nor is there any harm. Even a little of this righteousness protects one from great fear."
41,व्यवसायात्मिका बुद्धिरेकेह कुरूनन्दन ।बहुशाखा ह्यनन्ताश्च बुद्धयोऽव्यवसायिनाम् ॥ ४१ ॥,"The resolute intellect is single-minded, O joy of the Kurus, but the intellect of the irresolute is many-branched and endless."
42,यामिमां पुष्पितां वाचं प्रवदन्त्यविपश्चितः ।वेदवादरताः पार्थ नान्यदस्तीति वादिनः ॥ ४२ ॥,"The unwise speak flowery words, O Partha, delighting in the letter of the Vedas, declaring that there is nothing else."
43,कामात्मानः स्वर्गपरा जन्मकर्मफलप्रदाम् ।क्रियाविशेषबहुलां भोगैश्वर्यगतिं प्रति ॥ ४३ ॥,"Those who are full of desires, who consider heaven as the highest goal, and who engage in elaborate rituals for the sake of obtaining pleasure and power, aim towards rebirth as the result of their actions."
44,भोगैश्वर्यप्रसक्तानां तयापहृतचेतसाम् ।व्यवसायात्मिका बुद्धिः समाधौ न विधीयते ॥ ४४ ॥,"For those who are attached to pleasure and prosperity, and whose minds are carried away by such things, the resolute intelligence does not form in the meditative state."
45,त्रैगुण्यविषया वेदा निस्त्रैगुण्यो भवार्जुन ।निर्द्वन्द्वो नित्यसत्त्वस्थो निर्योगक्षेम आत्मवान् ॥ ४५ ॥,"The Vedas deal with the three modes of material nature. Be free from these three modes, O Arjuna. Be free from dualities, ever firm in purity, free from anxieties for gain and safety, and established in the self."
46,यावानर्थ उदपाने सर्वतः सम्प्लुतोदके ।तावान्सर्वेषु वेदेषु ब्राह्मणस्य विजानतः ॥ ४६ ॥,"All the purposes that a small well serves are equally served by a large body of water; similarly, all the purposes of the Vedas are fulfilled to the person who knows the essence of the Vedas."
47,कर्मण्येवाधिकारस्ते मा फलेषु कदाचन ।मा कर्मफलहेतुर्भूर्मा ते सङ्गोऽस्त्वकर्मणि ॥ ४७ ॥,"Your right is to perform your duty only, never to its fruits. Let not the fruits of action be your motive, nor let your attachment be to inaction."
48,योगस्थः कुरु कर्माणि सङ्गं त्यक्त्वा धनञ्जय ।सिद्ध्यसिद्ध्योः समो भूत्वा समत्वं योग उच्यते ॥ ४८ ॥,"Perform your duties while established in yoga, O Dhananjaya, abandoning attachment and being the same in success and failure. Such equanimity is called yoga."
49,दूरेण ह्यवरं कर्म बुद्धियोगाद्धनञ्जय ।बुद्धौ शरणमन्विच्छ कृपणाः फलहेतवः ॥ ४९ ॥,"Action is far inferior to the yoga of wisdom, O Dhananjaya. Seek refuge in wisdom; those who seek the fruits of their actions are miserable."
50,बुद्धियुक्तो जहातीह उभे सुकृतदुष्कृते ।तस्माद्योगाय युज्यस्व योगः कर्मसु कौशलम् ॥ ५० ॥,"Endowed with wisdom, one discards both good and evil deeds in this world. Therefore, engage in yoga, for yoga is skill in action. (Verse 50)"
51,कर्मजं बुद्धियुक्ता हि फलं त्यक्त्वा मनीषिणः ।जन्मबन्धविनिर्मुक्ताः पदं गच्छन्त्यनामयम् ॥ ५१ ॥,"Endowed with wisdom, the wise ones, having renounced the fruit born of actions, become free from the bondage of birth and attain the state beyond suffering."
52,यदा ते मोहकलिलं बुद्धिर्व्यतितरिष्यति ।तदा गन्तासि निर्वेदं श्रोतव्यस्य श्रुतस्य च ॥ ५२ ॥,"When your intellect crosses beyond the mire of delusion, then you shall attain indifference to what is to be heard and what has been heard."
53,श्रुतिविप्रतिपन्ना ते यदा स्थास्यति निश्चला ।समाधावचला बुद्धिस्तदा योगमवाप्स्यसि ॥ ५३ ॥,"When your mind, which is confused by hearing various teachings, becomes steady and firmly fixed in meditation, then you will achieve yoga."
54,अर्जुन उवाचस्थितप्रज्ञस्य का भाषा समाधिस्थस्य केशव ।स्थितधीः किं प्रभाषेत किमासीत व्रजेत किम् ॥ ५४ ॥,"Arjuna said: O Keshava, what is the description of one who is steady in wisdom and absorbed in meditation? How does a person of steady mind speak, sit, and walk?"
55,श्रीभगवानुवाचप्रजहाति यदा कामान्सर्वान्पार्थ मनोगतान् ।आत्मन्येवात्मना तुष्टः स्थितप्रज्ञस्तदोच्यते ॥ ५५ ॥,"The Blessed Lord said: When a person gives up all desires arising in the mind, O Partha, and is content in the self alone by the self, then he is said to be of steady wisdom."
56,दुःखेष्वनुद्विग्न‍मनाः सुखेषु विगतस्पृहः ।वीतरागभयक्रोधः स्थिधीर्मुनिरुच्यते ॥ ५६ ॥,"One whose mind is not disturbed in sorrow, who is free from desire in happiness, who is devoid of attachment, fear, and anger, is called a sage of steady wisdom."
57,यः सर्वत्रानभिस्नेहस्तत्तत्प्राप्य श‍ुभाश‍ुभम् ।नाभिनन्दति न द्वेष्टि तस्य प्रज्ञा प्रतिष्ठिता ॥ ५७ ॥,"He who is unattached everywhere, who, having obtained good and evil, neither rejoices nor hates, his wisdom is established."
58,यदा संहरते चायं कूर्मोऽङ्गानीव सर्वशः ।इन्द्रियाणीन्द्रियार्थेभ्यस्तस्य प्रज्ञा प्रतिष्ठिता ॥ ५८ ॥,"When one withdraws the senses from the objects of the senses, like a tortoise withdrawing its limbs from all sides, then his wisdom is firmly established."
59,विषया विनिवर्तन्ते निराहारस्य देहिनः ।रसवर्जं रसोऽप्यस्य परं दृष्ट्वा निवर्तते ॥ ५९ ॥,"The objects of the senses turn away from the abstinent person, leaving the longing behind; but the taste also turns away from him upon seeing the Supreme."
60,यततो ह्यपि कौन्तेय पुरुषस्य विपश्चितः ।इन्द्रियाणि प्रमाथीनि हरन्ति प्रसभं मनः ॥ ६० ॥,"Even for a person of wisdom who strives, O son of Kunti, the turbulent senses forcibly carry away the mind. (Chapter 2, Verse 60)"
61,तानि सर्वाणि संयम्य युक्त आसीत मत्परः ।वशे हि यस्येन्द्रियाणि तस्य प्रज्ञा प्रतिष्ठिता ॥ ६१ ॥,"Having restrained all the senses, he should sit, disciplined, with me as the supreme goal; for whose senses are controlled, his wisdom is firmly established."
62,ध्यायतो विषयान्पुंसः सङ्गस्तेषूपजायते ।सङ्गात्सञ्जायते कामः कामात्क्रोधोऽभिजायते ॥ ६२ ॥,"For a person who dwells on objects, attachment to them arises; from attachment, desire is born; from desire, anger arises."
63,क्रोधाद्भ‍वति सम्मोहः सम्मोहात्स्मृतिविभ्रमः ।स्मृतिभ्रंशाद्बुद्धिनाशो बुद्धिनाशात्प्रणश्यति ॥ ६३ ॥,"From anger arises delusion, from delusion, confusion of memory; from confusion of memory, loss of intellect; from loss of intellect, one perishes."
64,रागद्वेषविमुक्तैस्तु विषयनिन्द्रियैश्चरन् ।आत्मवश्यैर्विधेयात्मा प्रसादमधिगच्छति ॥ ६४ ॥,"One who moves among the objects of the senses with the senses under control, free from attachment and aversion, attains tranquility."
65,प्रसादे सर्वदुःखानां हानिरस्योपजायते ।प्रसन्नचेतसो ह्याश‍ु बुद्धिः पर्यवतिष्ठते ॥ ६५ ॥,"In tranquility, all sorrows are destroyed. Indeed, for the tranquil-minded, soon the intellect becomes well-established."
66,नास्ति बुद्धिरयुक्तस्य न चायुक्तस्य भावना ।न चाभावयतः शान्तिरशान्तस्य कुतः सुखम् ॥ ६६ ॥,"The one who is not united (with the Divine) lacks wisdom, and the one who is not united lacks contemplation. For the one who does not contemplate, there is no peace; and how can there be happiness for one who is not peaceful?"
67,इन्द्रियाणां हि चरतां यन्मनोऽनुविधीयते ।तदस्य हरति प्रज्ञां वायुर्नावमिवाम्भसि ॥ ६७ ॥,"For the mind that follows the wandering senses, it carries away one's wisdom, just as the wind carries away a boat on the water."
68,तस्माद्यस्य महाबाहो निगृहीतानि सर्वशः ।इन्द्रियाणीन्द्रियार्थेभ्यस्तस्य प्रज्ञा प्रतिष्ठिता ॥ ६८ ॥,"Therefore, O mighty-armed one, he whose senses are completely restrained from their objects, his wisdom is firmly established."
69,या निशा सर्वभूतानां तस्यां जागर्ति संयमी ।यस्यां जाग्रति भूतानि सा निशा पश्यतो मुनेः ॥ ६९ ॥,"That which is night for all beings, in that the disciplined one is awake; that in which beings are awake, is night for the sage who sees."
70,आपूर्यमाणमचलप्रतिष्ठंसमुद्रमापः प्रविशन्ति यद्वत् ।तद्वत्कामा यं प्रविशन्ति सर्वेस शान्तिमाप्‍नोति न कामकामी ॥ ७० ॥,"Just as the waters enter the ocean, which is being filled and yet remains steady, so also desires enter the person who has attained peace; not the one who is desirous of desires."
71,विहाय कामान्यः सर्वान्पुमांश्चरति निःस्पृहः ।निर्ममो निरहङ्कार स शान्तिमधिगच्छति ॥ ७१ ॥,"Abandoning all desires, the person who lives free from longing, without a sense of ""mine"" or egoism, attains peace."
72,एषा ब्राह्मी स्थितिःपार्थ नैनां प्राप्य विमुह्यति ।स्थित्वास्यामन्तकालेऽपि ब्रह्मनिर्वाणमृच्छति ॥ ७२ ॥,"This is the state of Brahman, O Partha; attaining this, one is not deluded. Being established in this state even at the end of life, one attains Brahman-nirvana."
